==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Syllepsis
<hw>Syl*lep"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>sy`llhpsis</grk> a taking together, from <?/. See
<er>syllable</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld>
<def>A figure of speech by which a word is used in a literal and
metaphorical sense at the same time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>The agreement of a verb or
adjective with one, rather than another, of two nouns, with either of
which it might agree in gender, number, etc.; as, <it>rex</it> et regina
<it>beati.</it></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sylleptical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Sylleptic</ent>⟦br⟧
